laboratory_examinations.findings: Transabdominal pelvic ultrasound shows a 9mm diameter blind-ending tubular structure in the right lower quadrant correlating with an abnormal appendix. The uterus measures 4.6 x 2.6 x 3.7 cm, normal thickened endometrium 0.3 cm, right ovary 2.4 x 2.2 x 2.2 cm, left ovary 2.7 x 2.8 x 2.5 cm. Normal arterial and venous waveforms in both ovaries. Doppler ultrasound demonstrates hyperemia in the appendix wall. No adjacent fluid collection.
1.4 mmol/L (within normal range of 0.5 to 2.0 mmol/L).
